# 6. React Server Components Improvements

## What are Server Components?

Normally:

```
Browser
 |
React Components
 |
API
 |
Database
```

Server Components allow:

```
Server
 |
React Component
 |
Database
```

Some components run only on the server.

Example:

```jsx
async function Users() {
  const users = await database.users.find();

  return (
    <div>
      {users.map((user) => (
        <p>{user.name}</p>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
}
```

Benefits:

- Less JavaScript sent to browser
- Faster loading
- Direct database access

---

# 7. Ref as a Prop

## Before:

You needed:

```jsx
forwardRef();
```

Example:

```jsx
const Input = forwardRef(function Input(props, ref) {
  return <input ref={ref} />;
});
```

---

React 19:

```jsx
function Input({ ref }) {
  return <input ref={ref} />;
}
```

Benefits:

- Simpler components
- Less code
- Easier component APIs

