# 8. Improved Hydration Errors

## What is hydration?

Hydration happens when React connects JavaScript to server-generated HTML.

Example:

Server sends:

```html
<h1>Hello</h1>
```

Browser expects:

```html
<h1>Hi</h1>
```

React detects mismatch.

Before:

```
Hydration failed.
```

Not very helpful.

React 19:

```
Expected server HTML:
<h1>Hello</h1>

Client rendered:
<h1>Hi</h1>
```

Much easier debugging.

